  "prompt": "How can you look more italian?",
  "response": "To look more Italian, you might consider:\n\n1. Fashion choices\n- Wear well-fitted, stylish clothing\n- Choose designer brands or classic Italian styles\n- Use accessories like scarves or sunglasses\n- Opt for dark colors or neutral tones\n\n2. Hair and grooming\n- Dark, well-styled hair\n- Neat facial hair or clean-shaven look\n- Maintain a sophisticated, polished appearance\n\n3. Physical characteristics\n- While genetics play a big role, you can:\n- Maintain a healthy, athletic build\n- Have a slightly olive or tanned complexion\n- Style your hair in a typically Mediterranean way\n\n4. Body language\n- Use more expressive hand gestures\n- Stand confidently\n- Appear passionate and animated when speaking\n\n5. Makeup (for women)\n- Natural, elegant makeup\n- Bold eyebrows\n- Sophisticated, understated look\n\nRemember, these are stereotypes and generalizations. Italians have diverse appearances, and looking \"Italian\" is subjective.",
